  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2008-05-07",
    "date": "2008-09-09T16:37:31Z",
    "text": "Medicare IVIG Access Act of 2008 - Amends title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act to direct the Secretary of Health and Human Services, upon collection of data and completion of a review, to provide, if appropriate, to physicians and hospitals furnishing intravenous immune globulins (IVIGs), an additional payment for all items related to the furnishing of IVIG in an appropriate amount.\n\nProvides for coverage of IVIG administered in the home.\n\nMakes disposable drug delivery systems, including elastomeric infusion pumps, for the treatment of colorectal cancer \u0093durable medical equipment\u0094 for Medicare purposes."
  },
